init_oa_special_rule(25.10)                        init_oa_special_rule(25.10)

Name
       init_oa_special_rule

Syntax
       init_oa_special_rule name

       Type: String

       Specifies  the  special rule to be used in OpenAccess to define the via
       search order for power routing. Typically used to specify a metal stack
       LEFSpecialRouteSpec type constraint group to read from  the  technology
       library  if  the  library contains multiple metal stacks. If nothing is
       specified, then the constraint group with the name  LEFSpecialRouteSpec
       is searched in OpenAccess. It is used by the init_design command.

Related Information
              * init_design

